# REVIEW.md — house conventions for code review

Drop this file at the root of a repo to customize how the `review` skill reviews
changes there. Gets concatenated into `CONVENTIONS.md` in every review bundle
and is treated as the highest-priority instruction set, overriding the generic
prompt where they conflict.

## Skip paths

Do not review changes under these paths:

- `dist/`, `build/`, `coverage/`
- `*.generated.ts`, `*.pb.go`
- `vendor/`, `node_modules/`, lockfiles

## Caps

- Max 3 nit-severity findings total (override default of 5).
- Do not flag missing tests for files under `scripts/`.

## Mandatory checks

- All HTTP handlers must validate input at the boundary — flag any new handler
  that reads `req.body` / query params without a schema check.
- Any new SQL string must be parameterized — flag any string concatenation or
  template interpolation into a query.
- New environment variable reads must have a default or fail fast at startup —
  flag `process.env.X` used without either.

## Tone

- Be terse. One sentence per `description` unless genuinely more is needed.
- Skip "consider" / "might want to" — state the issue directly.
